 caption)

A POEM FOR ME.

Looking at you casually write
the most unheard things and poems of this world,
I see, no, I hear
your heart beating so loudly
for literature
hungry for knowledge
hungry for the intellect of this entire world

The subtle way of yours
to dangerously say "You're too kind"
as if you don't deserve that love
or appreciation others have for you

Why I wonder, are you so humble, no unkind
to yourself, to your words, to your godly talent
Why won't you believe when someone calls you beautiful
or compliments you something other than "cute"
I can only wonder
That's all I will ever do.

But you, my dear best friend since birth,
when you look at the mirror,
why don't you see what I can so evidently observe
your natural hair is something I desire
and your grace is something from the fire

Your appetite isn't big, don't starve yourself 
just for other's sake
You'll end up hurting yourself
You are hurting yourself
When will you ever understand?

When will you finally understand
that the tears from your eyes are pearls
and the blood running in your veins is gold,
the handwriting you have when you're tired
is something so many secretly admire

So, I hope the next time, someone says
"You're beautiful" or "I love you",
you don't deny those facts
just because one person hurt you in the past

Just because someone didn't intend to love 
doesn't mean love doesn't exist
and just because others were unkind to you
doesn't mean you don't deserve it from yourself

